{{fbdoc item="title" value="RGB"}}----
Function to compute valid color value for hi/truecolor modes.

{{fbdoc item="syntax"}}##
	[[KeyPgPpdefine #define]] **RGB**(//r//,//g//,//b//) (([[KeyPgCuint cuint]](r) [[KeyPgShl shl]] 16) [[KeyPgOr or]] ([[KeyPgCuint cuint]](g) [[KeyPgShl shl]] 8) [[KeyPgOr or]] [[KeyPgCuint cuint]](b) [[KeyPgOr or]] &hFF000000)
##
{{fbdoc item="usage"}}##
	**RGB**(//red//, //green//, //blue//)
##
{{fbdoc item="param"}}
	##//red//##
		red colour component value
	##//green//##
		green colour component value
	##//blue//##
		blue colour component value

{{fbdoc item="ret"}}
	the combined colour

{{fbdoc item="desc"}}
	##//Red//##, ##//green//## and ##//blue//## are components ranging 0-255.

	The ##**RGB**## function can be used to compute a valid color value for use while in hi/truecolor modes. It returns an integer  in the format &hAARRGGBB, where RR, GG and BB equals the values passed to this function, in hexadecimal format. AA is the implicit alpha value and is automatically set to &hFF.

Example:
	See ##[[KeyPgPutgraphics Put (Graphics)]]## example in addition.

{{fbdoc item="ex"}}
%%(qbasic)
ScreenRes 640,480,32  '32 bit color
Line(0,0)-(319,479), Rgb(255,0,0) 'draws a bright red box on the left side of the window
Line(639,0)-(320,479), Rgb(0,0,255) 'draws a bright blue box on the right side of the window

Sleep 'wait before exiting
%%

